SUMMARY:Swarthmore LGBTQ Alum Book Club
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['College Advancement']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel
  Discussion\\nSwarthmore LGBTQ Alum Book Club Presents: Transgender Histor
 ies from Late Imperial China with Matthew Sommer ’83 RSVP! About the Tal
 kJoin Matthew Sommer ’83 and Adrianne Pierce ’84 for a deep dive into 
 Matthew’s groundbreaking book\, The Fox Spirit\, the Stone Maiden\, and 
 Other Transgender Histories from Late Imperial China. Winner of several aw
 ards\, including the 2025 John K. Fairbank Prize in East Asian history\, a
 nd a finalist for the 2025 Lambda Literary Award\, this work is an unprece
 dented study of transgender lives and practices in late imperial China. Ma
 tthew considers a range of experiences\, illuminating how certain forms of
  gender transgression were sanctioned in particular social contexts and pe
 nalized in others. A remarkable account of China’s transgender histories
 \, Matthew sheds new light on a range of themes in Ming and Qing law\, rel
 igion\, medicine\, literature\, and culture. Matthew Sommer ’83 is the B
 owman Family Professor of History at Stanford University.\\nDetails: https
 ://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D140277
 8071
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1402778071
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
