SUMMARY:Summer 2026 Workshop Series: Navigating Unexpected Challenges
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"\, 'Beyond The Classroom'\, 'D
 ivision of Student Affairs']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nTuesda
 ys and Thursdays in Sci 101 from 12-1:30pm. Lunch will be provided. We all
  know that life doesn’t always follow a script! This workshop will help 
 you develop skills to navigate around obstacles or unexpected challenges. 
 We’ll explore distress tolerance\, emotion regulation\, and how to ask f
 or help so you can move from overwhelm into action. Presented by Simone Co
 llins\, Director of Counseling & Psychological Services\, and Josh Ellow\,
  Associate Director\, Wellness Assessment & Compliance & Alcohol & Other D
 rug Counselor.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=
 view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1395671884
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1395671884
