SUMMARY:Swarthmore Summer Scholars Program (S3P) Poster Session
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Poster Session\\
 nThe Swarthmore Summer Scholar Program (S3P) invites the campus community 
 to visit our Annual Poster Session on Friday\, August 1st from 10am-11:30a
 m in Singer Atrium. This July\, the S3P Scholars have been learning about 
 how cells divide. For their culminating projects\, they are designing\, co
 nducting\, and analyzing their own experiments to examine the effects of c
 hemicals on cell division. Please drop in anytime between 10am and 11:30am
  to meet this amazing cohort of incoming first-year students and see what 
 they’ve discovered! We are excited to see you there!  The Annual Swarthm
 ore Summer Scholars Program Poster Session Celebrating the S3P Class of 20
 29 Friday\, August 1\, 10am-11:30am\, Singer Atrium  \\nDetails: https://
 swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D139274555
 0
LOCATION:Singer First Floor Commons
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1392745550
CATEGORIES:Poster Session
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2e1bf7210f75502d@swarthmore-dash-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260610T142610Z
DTSTART:20260802T200000Z
DTEND:20260802T210000Z
SUMMARY:CCC Presents The Sky Brooks Quartet
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Chester Children's Chorus"]\\nCategory: Perform
 ance\\nEnjoy an afternoon with The Skyy Brooks Quartet featuring jazz favo
 rites and special arrangements\, including "My Funny Valentine\," "I Didn'
 t Know What Time It Was\," "How High The Moon\," "If I Were A Bell\," "Bla
 ckbird\," and "A House Is Not A Home." Come hear Skyy and Chester Children
 's Chorus Executive and Artistic Director John Alston perform their very f
 avorite songs\, and maybe yours too!   Skyy is a CCC alumna and recent g
 raduate of both Harvard University and Berklee College of Music\, where sh
 e studied African American Studies and Contemporary Vocal Performance\, re
 spectively. Admission is free. Seating is on a first-come\, first-served b
 asis.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Dev
 ent%26eventid%3D1395474333
LOCATION:Lang Music Building Room 214-Presser Room\, Lang Music Concert Hal
 l\, Lang Music Building Upper Lobby\, Lang Music Building Lower Lobby
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1395474333
CATEGORIES:Performance
END:VEVENT
